algorithm: The new algorithm assigns scores to each bin based on the logarithm of the bin capacity divided by the absolute difference between the bin capacity and the item size, then raises this value to the power of the square root of the item size divided by the bin capacity. The scores of each bin are then normalized by dividing them by the maximum score across all bins.
code:
import numpy as np

def score(item: int, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    # Calculate the scores for the bins
    scores = np.log(bins / np.abs(bins - item)) ** (np.sqrt(item) / bins)
    
    # Normalize the scores by dividing by the maximum score
    max_score = np.max(scores)
    scores = scores / max_score
    
    return scores
